<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Table Tennis "Union" Disbanded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EINDHOVEN, Netherlands, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The Club of Table
Tennis Professionals (CTTP), which served as a union for table tennis
players, has been disorganized, CTTP Management Committee announced
here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Club was founded in 1992 and had been working for better
working conditions of the professional table tennis players. The
Management Committee didn't give the reason of disbanding in its
statement.
</P>
<P>
The Club, which registered a membership of 151 in 1998, had played
an important role in the raising of the glue ban by the International
Table Tennis Federation (ITTF).
</P>
<P>
The table tennis ruling body ITTF had imposed a ban on
speed-and-spin enhancing glues but later gave in while facing strong
opposition from CTTP and table tennis manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
World-class table tennis players including Andrzej Grubba of
Poland, Steffen Fetzner of Germany, Jean-Michel Saive of Belgium.
Jean-Philippe Gatien of France and Jorgen Persson of Sweden had
involved in the CTTP Management Committee, the statement said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
