<HEADLINE> Asian Recovery Helps Banking Giant HSBC Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A recovery in the Far East economy
and a strong performance in the west saw HSBC record a 10 percent
rise in pre-tax profits for the six months to June.
</P>
<P>
The 10 percent jump in pre-tax profits for the six months to
over 4 billion U.S. dollars was also aided by the group's UK
buiness, formerly known as Midland Bank, which it said "continued
to perform strongly."
</P>
<P>
According to HSBC's Interim Report released Monday, the pre-tax
profits from the business were ahead 12 percent to 1.45 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
John Bond, HSBC Holdings chairman, said, "For the first time in
our history, operating profits before provisions approached 5
billion U.S. dollars for a six month period."
</P>
<P>
The group was now looking to expand in the U.S. and Thailand,
although "nothing firm is on the table" at the moment, Bond said.
</P>
<P>
Economists in the City believe that the group is looking at a
range of possibilities around the world and likely to come to the
markets at some point in the second half. 
</P>
</TEXT>
