<HEADLINE> Congolese Rebels Welcome Bemba's Signing of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 2 (Xinhua) --The rival groups within the rebel
Congolese Rally for Democracy (CRD) have said they welcome the
signing by the rebel Movement for the Liberation for Congo (MLC)
of the Lusaka cease-fire agreement.
</P>
<P>
Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation Monday quoted CRD
leader Emile Illunga as saying that although the signing came as a
surprise, it is in line with the peace plan initiated by Zambian
President Frederick Chiluba.
</P>
<P>
Another CRD group leader Ernest Wamba Dia Wamba said that he
appreciated the signing of the agreement by MLC leader Jean-Pierre
Bemba here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The six warring countries involved in the 11-month war in
Democratic Republic of Congo signed the cease-fire agreement in
Zambian capital Lusaka on July 10 this year.
</P>
<P>
The CRD and the MLC did not sign the agreement because of the
disagreement within CRD over who would on behalf of the CRD sign
the agreement.
</P>
<P>
CRD split into two factions in May this year -- one led by
Emile Illunga and the other by Ernest Wamba Dia Wamba.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources said that the CRD rebels are expected to
sign the cease-fire agreement before August 7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
