<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean President Commissions China-Aid Furnace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe
Monday opened Blast Furnace No. 4 of the Zimbabwe Iron and Steel
Company (ZISCO) in Kwekwe of central Zimbabwe, expressing his
gratitude to the Chinese government for all the support it has
given over the project.
</P>
<P>
The president said that the Chinese government and China
Shougang (Capital) Corporation have been very supportive in the
rehabilitation program of the Zimbabwean iron and steel company.
</P>
<P>
"The completion of the rehabilitation of Blast Furnace No. 4 is
a key element in the modernization of the entire production
process at ZISCO," said Mugabe.
</P>
<P>
"In terms of production, I am informed that the capacity of
Blast Furnace No. 4 will satisfy the market demand for long
products of Zimbabwe and the whole Common Market for East and
Southern Africa (COMESA) region," he said.
</P>
<P>
"This will be a very positive development since these markets
have been experiencing insufficient supplies of billets and other
finished products," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that "70 percent of output will be exported, mainly as
billets to overseas markets, earning the country much in foreign
currency."
</P>
<P>
He said for the ZISCO, 1999 is the year in which the company is
expected to make a U-turn from a loss making to a profit making
company.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony, Chinese Ambassador to Harare Huang
Guifang said the Chinese government provided 35 million U.S.
dollars for the project.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said that the ZISCO is one of the largest
parastatal of Zimbabwe, which plays a very important role in the
economic development of the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
"The giant parastatal was facing tremendous difficulties after
its lifeline -- Blast Furnace No. 4 collapsed in 1993. With a
close cooperation between China and Zimbabwe, the rehabilitation
of the blast furnace was brought to a reality," he said.
</P>
<P>
He believed that the ZISCO will be reincarnated along with the
reopening of blast furnace No. 4 and make more contributions to
the prosperity of Zimbabwe's economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
