<DOCNO> XIE19990803.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Defective Eclipse Glasses Detected in Belgium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Some 1,000 pairs of anti-retina
burnt glasses with defects were found in Belgium by Monday,
arousing scare among local health authorities.
</P>
<P>
The solar eclipse-oriented glasses, together with another 2,000
pairs now for sale in local shops, were found to be defective
after being imported from Colombia.
</P>
<P>
Local health authorities appealed to the buyers of the
defective glasses to denounce their purchases and not to use them
on August 11 while witnessing the solar eclipse.
</P>
<P>
Looking into the solar eclipse without protective glasses or
with defective glasses can cause serious eye problems such as
retina burnts that may be a lasting damage, eye specialists
warned.
</P>
<P>
Sales of solar eclipse glasses picked up a week ago when local
people started to prepare for the coming solar eclipse on August
11.
</P>
<P>
Solar eclipse watchers were suggested to go to the south of the
country, especially to a town known as Virton to have a better
view of the rare phenomenon that takes place at an interval of an
average of 370 years.
</P>
<P>
A solar eclipse happens when the moon travels right in between
the sun and the earth, blocking the view of the sun from the
earth.
</P>
<P>
The August 11 solar eclipse is estimated to be visible in whole
or in part to around 2 billion residents of this planet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990803.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Rush for Resolving Kalapani Issue: Indian Ambassador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- India is confident that the
Kalapani territorial dispute will be resolved, but it is premature
to solve it right now, said the Indian Ambassador to Nepal Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in a face-to-face talk with journalists, K.V. Rajan
said that he is confident that the Kalapani issue will be properly
resolved, but it needs time.
</P>
<P>
He said India is ready to listen to Nepal's arguments about the
Kalapani issue and will respect Nepal's stand on it.
</P>
<P>
Joint studies about whether the disputed area belongs to India
or Nepal is going on, said the ambassador.
</P>
<P>
Both India and Nepal lay claim to the Kalapani area in
far-western Nepal which is now occupied by Indian troops.
</P>
<P>
The overall relationship between India and Nepal is friendly
and there are no basic differences between the two countries,
added the ambassador, citing recent positive development on
transit treaty as an example.
</P>
<P>
As for Bhutanese refugees, the ambassador insisted that it is a
bilateral issue between Bhutan and Nepal and India will stick to a
non-involvement policy on this issue.
</P>
<P>
He said that India is not ready to mediate the issue of
Bhutanese refugees.
</P>
<P>
"If India wants to help, what will we do about it?" he asked.
</P>
<P>
More than 100,000 Bhutan refugees are now living in eastern
Nepal after they were forced to flee Bhutan around 1990. Seven
rounds of talks on repatriation between the two Himalayan kingdoms
have so far ended in failure.
</P>
<P>
Nepal sought India's help in resolving the refugee issue, but
India, which handles Bhutan's foreign affairs, refused to be
involved in the matter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
