<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Central Bank Warns Fake Notes in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Zambia has warned the
public to be aware of the counterfeit kwacha notes in circulation
when transacting in bank notes.
</P>
<P>
The notes which were most used to the fraud were the 500
kwacha, 5000 kwacha and 10,000 kwacha denominations, public
relations manager of the central bank, Kabinga Pande told Xinhua
Monday at the just ended 73rd Zambia Agricultural and Commercial
Show in Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
But the bank official said that he was not so sure whether the
reproduction was being done locally or internationally.
</P>
<P>
A huge amount of the fake notes had been confiscated
nationwide, he added.
</P>
<P>
Pande noted that the amount of the fake notes the central bank
had recorded was incomparable to the total notes in circulation.
</P>
<P>
"We are working hand in hand with security agents to get to the
bottom of this scam. Though none has been charged for printing
false money, one or two people have been charged for transacting
counterfeit notes," he added.
</P>
<P>
Viewed under ultra-violet light, the watermark of a fish
eagle's head and the national court of arms is visible on the
genuine kwacha notes, he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
