<HEADLINE> Di Pasquale Upsets Top See Hrbaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Arnaud di Pasquale of France
upset top seed Dominik Hrbaty of Slovak 6-2, 6-3 in the opening
match of the Dutch Open clay court tennis tournament in Amsterdam
of the Netherlands, Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Slovak failed to find the form he showed at the French Open
in May where he advanced to the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Hrbaty, ranked 19 in the world, lost the opening set 6-2 and
had to fight off three matchpoints at 5-1 in the second set to
break Di Pasquale.
</P>
<P>
But in the ninth game of that set the 56th-ranked Frenchman
closed out the match 6-3 on his own serve to move into the second
round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
