<P>
Germany's electronically-traded Xetra Dax finished 27 points
higher at 5129.5, a gain of 0.5 percent, having traded close to 3
percent lower.
</P>
<P>
Paris was the only bourse to close in the red on the day, with
the leading CAC 40 index reversing all but the smallest losses as
it closed 4 points lower at 4377.87. 
