<HEADLINE> Israel Soccer Club Docked Points over Doping Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Maccabi Tel Aviv soccer
club was docked four league points by a Israel Football
Association on Tuesday, and the soccer team also was suspended
another four points and fined by 100,000 shekels (23,900 U.S.
dollars) over doping offenses.
</P>
<P>
Maccabi, who finished second in the league to Hapoel Haifa last
season, are one of Israel's two representatives in this season's
UEFA Cup.
</P>
<P>
The IFA launched a two-month inquiry involving the club,their
former fitness trainer and a player after midfielder Kfir Edri, 22,
tested positive for the stimulant ephedrine following the club's
match at Hapoel Haifa in May.
</P>
<P>
The disciplinary court barred Edri, who said he was unaware of
taking a banned substance, for six matches. Guy Azuri, a former
Maccabi fitness trainer, has been banned for two years.The pair
can only appeal after serving half their punishments.
</P>
<P>
Maccabi's first UEFA opponents are Kaunas of Lithuania with a
match in the qualifying round. They meet in Israel in the first
leg on August 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
