<HEADLINE> About 743,000 Ethnic Albanian Refugees Return to Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 3 (Xinhua) -- About 743,000 ethnic Albanian
refugees have returned to Kosovo since the end of NATO's air
campaign against Yugoslavia early June, the Moscow office of the U.
N. High Commissioner for Refugees said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 54,600 refugees returned from Montenegro, 516,500
from Macedonia, 433,300 from Albania, and 9,600 from Bosnia, the
Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Slatina, the airport of the Kosovo capital of Pristina, has
been receiving planes loaded with returning refugees every day,
the office said. 
