<HEADLINE> Three Killed in Road Accident in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and four
others injured when a minibus overturned in Menia Governorate, 220
kilometers south of Cairo on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The minibus overturned after a front wheel blew up, Egypt's
Middle East News Agency quoted security sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the injured have been rushed to a hospital and
further investigation is underway into the mishap.
</P>
<P>
In another accident, a freight train derailed after hitting and
destroying the bumper at the Balana station near Aswan, a town 700
kilometers south of the capital, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place when the train tried to shunt for a
sleeper traveling to Aswan from Cairo and ran into the bumper in
the process.
</P>
<P>
No casualties were reported in the accident, which resulted in
disruption of railway traffic in the area for four hours. 
