<HEADLINE> HK Plans China's National Day Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) government will organize a series of
civic education activities to mark the 50th anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic of China on October 1, to
promote a better understanding of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The celebration program, mainly targets at the younger
generation, has adopted the theme "Hearts and Hopes for Motherland
and Hong Kong".
</P>
<P>
The program aims to provide the public with a special
opportunity to participate in the National Day celebrations in
Hong Kong and at the same time acquire a better understanding of
China, ranging from the country's history and traditions to its
latest political, economic and social development through a wide
variety of events.
</P>
<P>
"To tie in with the major celebration activities on October 1,
this civic education program would urge the public, in particular
youths, to learn more about our motherland which in turn would
foster a stronger sense of belonging to Hong Kong and contribute
to the implementation of the 'one country, two systems' principle,
" said David Lan, secretary for home affairs, while announcing the
details of the program at a press conference Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The program consists of two phases of activities. The first
phase includes the Tokens of Regards Design Competition and youth
camp to be held during the summer vacation while the second phase
will be highlighted by the National Day Celebration Week starting
from September 25 to October 3.
</P>
<P>
The week, spanning the two weekends before and after the
National Day, covers activities which are both interesting and
informative. There will be exhibitions, lectures, a Chinese art
market, concerts, dance performances, films and a Chinese food
fiesta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
