</P>
<P>
According to a report of the Afghan Islamic Press (AIP), the
student militia are heading towards Dashte-Arche, another district
of Kunduz.
</P>
<P>
During the overnight fighting, the Taliban gained the control
over Sher Khan Bandar in Kunduz which had been used to ship
outside supplies to the anti-Taliban northern alliance forces.
</P>
<P>
The alliance commander Ahmad Shah Masood developed another
port, Aaye Khanam in Takhar province, on the same river two years
ago which weakened the importance of Sher Khan Bandar, according
to Afghan sources here.
</P>
<P>
On the main battlefields north of the capital Kabul, Taliban
troops were carrying out clean-up operations, reported AIP.
</P>
<P>
The militia claimed that they had entered into strategic Salang
Pass, which connects the northern part of Afghanistan with Kabul,
but no immediate confirmation from independent sources was
available.
</P>
<P>
AIP said the Taliban forces also captured the Parwan province
town of Gulbahar at the mouth of the Panjsher valley, the
opposition stronghold which the Masood forces had retreated into.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
