<HEADLINE> Malaysia Plans New Millennium Celebrations to Boost Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will celebrate the
advent of the new millennium on a grand scale with various
programs aimed at promoting the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
The celebration, called "Malaysia's Centennial Into The New
Millennium", will be held for two years from September this year
to August 2001, Malaysian Deputy Prime Minister Abdullah Ahmade
Badawi said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The main objective of the program is to raise awareness of and
love for one's own country among Malaysians and also to draw the
attention of the world community to the achievements of the
Malaysian race, he told reporters after chairing the inaugural
meeting of the celebrations committee at Putrajaya, the new
government center, some 30 kilometers from here, the Malaysian
national news agency Bernama reported.
</P>
<P>
It is also to inculcate the tourism culture among Malaysians to
enjoy the beauty of their own country and to lure the world
community to visit Malaysia and thus step up the nation's tourism
industry, he said.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah said the government would also use the opportunity to
organize visits before and after the international-class events to
introduce Malaysia to the visitors.
</P>
<P>
All events under the "Malaysia's Centennial Into The New
Millennium" program would be coordinated by the Culture, Arts and
Tourism Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The programs already planned for this year include the two-week
Malaysia Fest starting on September 11 and culminating with the
Colors of Malaysia Parade on September 25. 
</P>
