<HEADLINE> Agriculture, Health Officials Slam Lee Teng-hui's Splittist Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Leading Chinese officials and
experts in the fields of agriculture and public health
respectively denounced Lee Teng-hui's splittist remarks here today,
saying that his "two states" statement has destroyed healthy cross-
straits cooperation in these fields.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Agriculture Chen Yaobang told a seminar that China'
s inland areas and Taiwan share a promising future of cooperation
in agriculture on a mutually beneficial basis.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 agricultural symposiums and trade talks between
the two sides of the Taiwan Straits have been held since 1988.
Agricultural personnel from both sides have a better understanding
of each other, and have established closer relations through
increased visits and academic exchanges, according to Xiang
Chongyang, chairman of the China Association for Agricultural
Exchanges.
</P>
<P>
However, this healthy development has been damaged since Lee
Teng-hui made his "two states" remarks, which deserves
denunciation by the people of both sides, Chen Yaobang said.
</P>
<P>
At another seminar, Health Minister Zhang Wenkang also noted
that the cross-straits cooperation in the field of medicine and
health care "have been set back by Lee Teng-hui's fallacies".
</P>
<P>
The participants in the seminars agreed that Lee's action not
only goes against the will of all Chinese people, including the
Taiwan compatriots, for the final reunification of China, but also
harms the fundamental interests of the people of the island
province.
</P>
<P>
They pointed out that, with a strong national cohesiveness, the
Chinese people are both determined to safeguard and capable of
safeguarding the territorial and sovereign integrity of China.
</P>
</TEXT>
