<HEADLINE> China to Hold Choir Festival for Elderly People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Culture will hold
the first choir festival for the elderly people in China this week
to promote a healthy and happy lifestyle among the aged population.
</P>
<P>
The festival will be the first of a series of cultural and
artistic activities of the International Year of Older Persons
1999. The other activities include poetry and painting contests,
fashion shows for the elderly and photo exhibitions which reflect
senior people's lives.
</P>
<P>
China has the largest aged population in the world, with more
than 120 million people, or one-tenth of its population, above 60
years old. The aged population in China is estimated to reach 400
million by the middle of the next century.
</P>
<P>
Comfortable living conditions for senior people are vital to
social stability and development, said an official with the
Ministry of Culture, adding that the series of cultural and
artistic activities is aimed at encouraging senior people to live
positive and rich spiritual lives.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,000 people from 60 chorus groups will attend a
grand performance of the chorus festival on August 8 and the China
Central Television Station will broadcast the performance.
</P>
</TEXT>
