<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Down 0.3 Percent in May 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The volume of Hong Kong's re-
exports in May 1999 increased by 1.7 percent over a year earlier,
and that of domestic exports fell by 12.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Taken together, the volume of Hong Kong's total exports in May
1999 decreased by 0.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the volume of imports dropped by 9.1 percent,
according to statistics released Tuesday by the Census and
Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the first five months of 1999 with the same period a
year earlier, the volume of Hong Kong's re-exports decreased by 2.
6 percent, and the volume of domestic exports by 10.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Taken together, the volume of total exports decreased by 3.7
percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, imports fell by 10.3 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Comparing May 1999 with May 1998, the prices of re-exports and
domestic exports fell by 3.8 percent and 2.9 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, import prices also declined by 3.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
As regards price changes in the first five months of 1999 over
the same period a year earlier, the prices of re-exports and
domestic exports were down by 4.3 percent and 2.8 percent
respectively, and import prices by 3.5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
