<HEADLINE> EDS-Recast China's Catholics Criticize Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Chinese Catholic
community have criticized the malicious fallacies of the Falun
Gong cult and said that banning it will not adversely affect
freedom of religious beliefs and normal religious activities in
China.
</P>
<P>
Jin Luxian, a member of the Standing Committee of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) and honorary chairman of the Chinese Patriotic
Catholic Association, said that Falun Gong is not a religion, but
an illegal organization that is like a cult.
</P>
<P>
Jin, who is a bishop of Shanghai parish, said that Falun Gong's
founder, Li Hongzhi, used religious terminology and mixed it with
his fallacies and this is against science, civilization, the state,
and even religion. Jin said he will try to get the 140,000
Catholics in Shanghai see the essence and danger of Falun Gong to
ensure the purity of religious faith.
</P>
<P>
The ban on the Falun Gong cult is a good thing, said Luo
Guanzong, who is also a member of the Standing Committee of the
CPPCC National Committee and chairman of the Three-self Patriotic
Movement Committee of the Protestant Churches of China. He said
that this action removes a problem from society and helps
implement China's religious policy.
</P>
<P>
Cao Shengjie, the chairman of the Shanghai Assembly of Church
of Christ, voiced strong support for the ban and said that
Christians should be careful and never accept fallacies mixed with
religious expressions.
</P>
<P>
Shen Derong, the chairman of the Three-self Patriotic Movement
of the Protestant Churches of Shanghai, said that the Christians
of Shanghai support the government ban and that cults should never
be allowed in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
