<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Buddhists Support Falun Gong Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Buddhist leaders have
given their support to the campaign against Falun Gong and say
they will help maintain social stability.
</P>
<P>
Jamyang Losang Jigme Tubdain Qoigyi Nyima, vice-president of
the Buddhist Association of China, accused of Li Hongzhi and Falun
Gong under his control of spreading feudalism and superstition
under the guise of teaching qigong and of taking advantage of
people's desire to stay healthy.
</P>
<P>
Li deceived many followers and caused some people to go insane
and has ruined many families, Jamyang said, pointing out that he
took the Buddhist term "Falun" as a title for his illegal
organization and people should keep an eye out for his evil
purpose.
</P>
<P>
Sheng Hui, vice-president of the Buddhist Association of China,
says that Falun Gong not only deceived many people, but infringed
upon the freedom of religious belief of people.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi got followers to attack Party and government
headquarters and press organizations and violated the law and
caused serious damage to social stability, Sheng says.
</P>
<P>
Ming Shan, also vice-president of the Buddhist Association of
China, says that the true face of Li Hongzhi and Falun Gong have
been exposed and that people now have a clearer understanding of
Li's motive, which was to defraud people of their money and
undermine social stability.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese will fight any behavior that undermines social
stability, ethnic unity, and national reunification and the three
Buddhist leaders praised the Falun Gong ban, calling it a wise
decision. It is the Party's and the government's way of protecting
legitimate religious groups and normal religious activities, they
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
