<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Host 5th World Wushu Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will host the Fifth
World Wushu Championships on November 3 to 7 this year, announced
the organizers -- the Hong Kong Wushu Union Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,500 Wushu (Chinese martial arts) practitioners from 77
countries and regions will take part in the championships that
will include Taolu and Sanshou competitions.
</P>
<P>
Ian Fok, President of the Hong Kong Wushu Union, said the
International Wushu Federation was admitted as a member of the
International Olympic Committee in June this year.
</P>
<P>
The staging of the Fifth World Wushu Championships in Hong Kong
will go a long way in promoting Wushu as a future Olympic sport,
he added.
</P>
<P>
The bi-annual World Wushu Championships, which started in 1991,
is the official tournament of the International Wushu Federation.
The previous four championships were held in Beijing, Kuala Lumpur
of Malaysia, Baltimore in the United States and Rome of Italy.
</P>
