<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Movie About China's Nuclear Bomb Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- China has spent 15 million yuan
on a feature film about its first atom bomb program, which is
expected to be released for the 50th anniversary of the birth of
the People's Republic of China on October 1.
</P>
<P>
The "Birth of the Chinese A-bomb" is being produced by the
Beijing Film Studio to show how the Chinese independently
developed nuclear weapons without the use of foreign technology,
studio sources say.
</P>
<P>
The movie was shot in the Lop Nur area of Xinjiang, where China
exploded its first atom bomb on October 16, 1964.
</P>
<P>
Chen Guoxing, who is known for his film "Kong Fansen", directed
the film, which stars Li Xuejian, a populkar actor, in the lead as
a general.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that the film makes use of formerly confidential
documents and digital effects. It took more than a year to make.
</P>
</TEXT>
