<DOCNO> XIE19990803.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore's Law Body to Function as Int'l Arbitration Institution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore Academy of Law
(SAL) has taken over the responsibility for the Singapore
International Arbitration Center (SIAC) with effect from August 3,
1999, the government stated in a press release Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The government said this transfer of arbitration function from
the Economic Development Board and the Trade Development of
Singapore is designed to further enhance arbitration as a method
of alternative dispute resolution within the legal framework of
Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Remaining as an independent institution under the aegis of the
Singapore Academy of Law and functioning as a separate entity from
the Singapore Mediation Center (SMC), which promotes mediation and
provides mediation service, SIAC will continue to operate under
the legal framework set up in Singapore for the conduct of
international arbitration and enforcement of wards, it added.
</P>
<P>
International parties can therefore have their arbitration
cases decided here in accordance with the Model Law on
International Commercial Arbitration as adopted by the United
Nations Commission on International Trade Law (UNCITRAL) and other
well-recognized rules, it noted.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1991, SIAC facilitates resolution of disputes
through arbitration in international cases as well as domestic
cases. International arbitration cases involving non-Singaporean
parties account for 70 percent of SIAC's caseload. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
