<HEADLINE> Falun Gong Practitioners Break Away From Cult </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Many practitioners of Falun Gong
have awakened to the evil of the banned organization and have come
to see Li Hongzhi's scheme and how they were fooled.
</P>
<P>
Wang Shengli, a retired cadre in the city of Fuyang in east
China's Anhui Province, was a Falun Gong practitioner and a local
leader in the illegal organization, but he has given his support
to the ban.
</P>
<P>
He says that, after watching the CCTV special report on Li
Hongzhi, he got a clearer understanding of Falun Gong and its evil
political purposes. Wang has helped local governments teach people
to break away from Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
Wang is just one of thousands of former Falun Gong
practitioners who have changed their minds since the central
government declared Falun Gong to be an illegal organization on
July 22 and banned it.
</P>
<P>
Relatives of Falun Gong practitioners in northwest China's
Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region have accused Falun Gong of cheating
people out of their money and of causing deaths. A large number of
former Falun Gong practitioners were drawn into the organization
because of its claims about being able to cure diseases, but, this
turned out not to be true. Several Falun Gong practitioners in
Yinchuan, the capital of Ningxia, refused to go to hospital when
they were ill because of their deep faith in Li Hongzhi, and some
lost their lives because of this. Falun Gong was the real culprit,
their family members say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
