<HEADLINE> More Overseas Tourists Visit China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of overseas tourists
to China jumped a year-on-year 19.6 percent in June to hit 34.7
million.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 693,000 are foreigners, up 20.2 percent, 4.94
million from Hong Kong and Macao, up 19.4 percent, and 210,000
from Taiwan, up 23.5 percent, according to the latest statistics
from the National Tourism Administration.
</P>
<P>
During the period, Asian tourists to China surged by an average
28.9 percent, with Indonesian visitors surging 110.6 percent. And
tourists from 11 of China's 15 major overseas tourist markets
including Japan, the Republic of Korea, Russia, Germany and France,
witnessed two-digit growth.
</P>
<P>
In June, China earned 1.194 billion U.S. dollars from overseas
tourism, up 21.3 percent from the same month last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
