<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Expedition Beginning Research In Arctic Ocean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SNOW DRAGON SHIP, August 3 (Xinhua)-- The Chinese Arctic
expedition entered into the Arctic Ocean again and began its
research work in the Chukchi Sea early this morning.
</P>
<P>
Qin Weijia, an assistant to the chief scientist, said that the
expedition will focus on samples from floating ice and water and
the atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
He said that the ship's helicopter and boat will be used for
the research work for the first time in the Arctic region.
</P>
<P>
The expedition entered the Arctic Ocean in mid-July and
finished the first stage researches, but, because of the ice at 71
degrees north latitude, it could not go farther. It will try to
reach 74 degrees north latitude.
</P>
<P>
After 7 days, they will go to the Canadian port of Toktoyaktuk
for a rest. Then, they will return to the frozen area to finish
the research. 
</P>
</TEXT>
