<HEADLINE> Sharara Set to Take over Xu as ITTF President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EINDHOVEN, Netherlands, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Adham
Sharara is set to take over Chinese Xu Yinsheng as President of
the International Table Tennis Federation, an ITTF official said
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sharara, Deputy President and CEO of the world table tennis ruling
body, is the only candidate for the ITTF presidency which has been
held by table tennis legend Xu since former president Lollo Hamarlund
of Sweden died three years ago.
</P>
<P>
In the close-door ITTF meeting which will last to late afternoon,
Sharara will be elected as president and Xu given the title as
honorary president, said the ITTF official who declided to be named.
</P>
<P>
Vice President Hans Giesecke of Germany, the man in charge of
ITTF finance, will vie with the French Table Tennis Federation
president for the position vacated by Sharara.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Yang Shu'an, vice chairman of the Chinese Table Tennis
Federation, will run for ITTF Vice President, the ITTF officiala said.
</P>
