<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Starts Exporting TV Sets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia has become a
television sets exporter after the first batch of TV sets was
exported to Zimbabwe early this week.
</P>
<P>
About 100 21-inch TV sets were transported to Zimbabwe last
Sunday, Tebarek Hassen, executive manager of the United Tebarek
and Family Private Limited Company, told Xinhua Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Tebarek said Zimbabwean businessmen have signed an agreement
with his company to import 1,000 21-inch TV sets during the next
six months.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Zimbabwe, he said, Tanzania, among other African
 countries, is also conducting market studies to import TV sets
from the Ethiopian TV assembly plant, the first of its kind in the
Horn of Africa country.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian TV factory imports spare parts from Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Tebarek said the factory would beef up its effort to increase
its production capacity from 100 to 1,500 TV sets per day.
</P>
<P>
Established on May 8, 1999 with a capital of 4.5 million birr
(about 562, 000 U.S. dollars), the TV assembly plant is expecting
to employ as many as 1, 500 people following the completion of its
expansion program, Tebarek said. 
</P>
