years old, being caught between the conflict of two women -- his
mother and his grand-mother. This was the root for the "weak
points" of his personal life, she said.
</P>
<P>
-- The Palestinians have been annoyed by the evasiveness of
Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak, who promised to apply --
belatedly -- the Wye Plantation Agreements from September and to
pull out troops from West Bank from October. Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat said on Monday that he has suspected for a long time
that Israel was trying to "escape a complete application" of the
Wye agreements and was trying to elude some engagements it has
made.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- Commenting on the latest peak of ozone air pollution
suffered by several regions in France, French Minister of
Environment Dominique Voynet said that government officials and
parliament deputies should provide people with full information on
pollution as a priority of their work. She also suggested that the
people traveling in the current summer vacation season should use
public transport facilities to alleviate pollution.
</P>
<P>
-- One year after coming to power for re-establishing peace in
his country, Colombia's conservative president Andres Pastrana was
unable to put under control different armed gangs, including left-
wing guerrillas, an armed Christian group claiming at the same
time to be the admirers of Che Guevara, narcotic barons and drug
traffickers. 
</P>
