<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clan Fighting Kills 5 in Somali Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Violent armed clashes between
rival militiamen spread to the Karan district of North Mogadishu
late Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Five people including a woman were killed and 15 others were
wounded in the exchange of the heavy gunfire outside the capital
when Muse Sudi Yalahow's militiamen extorted money from an armed
militia escorted vehicle transporting commercial goods from
El-Ma'an natural port. The escort militiamen had refused to pay
the money which resulted in fighting.
</P>
<P>
Well armed militiamen from both sides using battle wagons,
Russian-made anti-tank B-10 guns, rocket propelled grenades, heavy
machine guns and assault rifles exchanged fire in the area.
</P>
<P>
Hussein Mohamed Addow, one of the main politicians of North
Mogadishu, together with various other politicians and traditional
leaders called the warring sides Monday night to an emergence
meeting to discuss ways to end the conflict.
</P>
<P>
Addow told reporters later that a cease-fire agreement has been
reached.
</P>
<P>
The security situation in North Mogadishu has been the worst in
the capital in the past few months after the collapse of the
strong Islamic court following the decree that sacked its
chairman two years ago. However, Islamic courts operating in
South Mogadishu have seriously curbed down the activities of the
bandits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
