<HEADLINE> 6 Killed, 9 Wounded in PKK Attack in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed and nine
others injured in an armed attack by the outlawed Kurdish Workers'
Party (PKK) in southeastern Turkey late Monday night.
</P>
<P>
A group of PKK rebels attacked a mini-bus at Cigdemli village in
Silvan town of Diyarbakir province, killing six people and
wounding nine others, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish security forces started a large-scale military
operation in a bid to capture the assailants, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting since 1984 a war for an independent
Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey. Its attacks on government
and civilian targets continue after PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan
was sentenced to death by Turkey's Ankara State Security Court in
June.
</P>
<P>
Conflicts between the Turkish security forces and the PKK
rebels have claimed over 37,000 lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
