<HEADLINE> China's Banks Being Encouraged To Support Processing Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC)
and the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation jointly
issued guidelines today encouraging banks to support Chinese
business development overseas.
</P>
<P>
A bank spokesman said that the guidelines aim to increase
exports and encourage China's light industry and textile, home
appliance, garment, and other manufacturers to develop processing
companies and assemblies overseas, using raw materials from China.
</P>
<P>
He said that, with the improvements in the economy and the
development of foreign trade and economic cooperation, processing
and assembly overseas are becoming increasingly important for
China's exports.
</P>
<P>
The guidelines say that commercial banks and the China Export
and Import Bank should give active support to these businesses
overseas and that long- and short-term loans are available for
purchasing equipment, technology, raw materials, and other items.
</P>
<P>
Processing and assembly businesses overseas that are making a
profit can pay less interest on the bank loans. Banks have been
asked to improve management of these loans to improve the quality
of their assets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
