<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Appointment Letter From Falun Gong Head Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, August 3 (Xinhua) -- One of the three letters of
appointment from Li Hongzhi, head of the Falun Gong cult, an
illegal organization, was found recently in Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi gave them to three people in the provincial capital,
Taiyuan, to appoint them leaders of the city's Falun Gong branch.
Provincial Public Security Bureau officials say that these letters
prove that Falun Gong is well organized.
</P>
<P>
The two other appoint letters were burned by the appointees.
</P>
<P>
The Public Security Bureau in China's Hunan Province has
obtained a list of addresses of Falun Gong leaders in the province,
according to a Bureau official.
</P>
<P>
He says that the list has names of members in 13 cities and
prefectures in Hunan and proves that Falun Gong is a tightly run
organization.
</P>
<P>
Falun Gong has said that it doesn't have any organization and
that it is managed in a loose way, but the evidence gathered by
public security departments in Hunan shows the opposite to be true.
</P>
<P>
It also shows that every Falun Gong branch has an organization
with propaganda, training, organization, and administration
sections, each with a clear duty. These branches cooperate and
communicate in a way that helped Falun Gong expand in such a short
period of time.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Sichuan Province Public Security Bureau say
that Falun Gong also has reserve forces, whose purpose is to avoid
investigation by public security departments and to continue the
illegal activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
