<HEADLINE> U.S. Peace Delegation Ends China Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A 34-member Children As
Peacemaker Fund delegation from the U.S. ended its China visit
today.
</P>
<P>
The delegation arrived here on July 28 to improve friendship
with the Chinese and to apologize for the U.S. bombing of the
Chinese embassy in Belgrade, Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
They attended children's activities and a flag raising ceremony
and climbed the Great Wall with a "flag of hope" to ask everyone
to safeguard world peace.
</P>
<P>
They came at the invitation of the All China Women's Federation.
The Children As Peacemaker Fund was established in 1982. 
</P>
