<HEADLINE> Another Chinese Golf Club Selected to World Top 100 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, Fujian Province, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Oriental
country club, which is based in Xiamen, a coastal city in
Southeast China, became the second Chinese club to join the Finest
Golf Clubs of the World (FGCW).
</P>
<P>
Of the 100 golf clubs on the Chinese mainland, Shenzhen-based
Wave-watching club was the other to be selected into FGCW, which
is composed of the top 100 clubs in the world.
</P>
<P>
The FGCW, which will go into official operation on the first
day of the upcoming millennium, was set up last year by three
prestigious bodies including Royal and Ancient Golf Association, U.
S. Golf Association and the Inside the Tour magazine.
</P>
<P>
They are the only three bodies which are entitled to appraise
and change the rules of world golf.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen Oriental country club, which occupies an area of 230
hectares, has made a success in organizing the Asian Pro Tour in
April 1998, the first Chinese club to achieve such feat.
</P>
<P>
Its court has been credited by experts as the most challenging
and professional and has been singled out for its membership
management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
