<HEADLINE> Beijing Scholars Blast Falun Gong (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Scholars from the Chinese Academy
of Social Sciences (CASS), China's highest research institution of
literary arts, today slammed the malicious fallacies of Li Hongzhi
and the banned Falun Gong he founded.
</P>
<P>
At a seminar held here, the scholars exposed the hideous
political nature of Falun Gong and lashed out at its grave harm to
society.
</P>
<P>
Chen Junquan, research fellow with the Philosophy Institute of
the CASS, said that the Falun Dafa concocted by Li directly
contradicts modern science and civilization and is simply a
fallacy, but a very dangerous one.
</P>
<P>
He said that social scientists need to stand up and expose and
criticize these fallacies and help the people get rid of this
inanity and promote scientific and healthy ways of living in the
country.
</P>
<P>
To peddle his fallacies, Li used many religious terms,
especially from Buddhism, but anyone with any religious sense
would see that Li was plagiarizing and wantonly twisting these
terms for his own evil purposes, said Zhang Xinying, a scholar who
studies the world's religions.
</P>
<P>
What Li has been doing is against society, the state, science,
and human beings and also seriously infringes upon the rights of
conventional religions and undermines China's religious policies,
Zhang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
