<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Has 61,600 Hectares of Cotton Fields </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh has brought 61,600
hectares of land under cotton cultivation during the season of
1999-2000, with the production target fixed at 141,850 bales, The
New Nation newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The cotton cultivation program will be monitored in 12 cotton
growing zones encompassing the 35 districts of the country with
proper government patronization and support, official sources were
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
On the average, the country produces 95,000 bales of cotton
annually, which can meet more than 12 percent of the total demand
of 600,000 bales, while the remaining 88 percent are imported,
according to Tofazzal Hossain, director of the Cotton Development
Board.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi government has taken a series of measures to
increase cotton production in a bid to gradually reduce the
dependence on cotton import, as the textile sector is growing
rapidly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
