<HEADLINE> Diplomats in Zambia Set up Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Diplomats here have formed an
association to get the diplomatic community closer, together with
their counterparts from international, regional organizations and
major firms.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Ambassador to Zambia Safwart Ayoub, who is one of the
board members of the grouping, told Xinhua by telephone Tuesday
that the body is to be called the Diplomatic Group of Lusaka
(DGL).
</P>
<P>
Among the functions of the group are: organizing
conferences-debates with eminent personalities from Zambia and
visiting Zambia including heads of states, preparing encounters in
sports as well as visits to selected sites of the country to
familiarize themselves with the various opportunities that Zambia
offers in tourism, but also in fields that could be developed.
</P>
<P>
Diplomats in Lusaka have welcomed the establishment of DGL and
promised to work together to serve the association, he said.
</P>
