<HEADLINE> Southern China Province Seizes Smuggled Goods In Scrap Metal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Customs officers in China's
Guangdong Province have stepped up efforts to deal with the
increasing amount of smuggled goods hidden in scrap metal
shipments.
</P>
<P>
The police tracked down and seized 14 shipments of this kind in
the first half of this year, with goods worth more than 10 million
yuan (about 1.2 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The illegal cargo hidden in among the scrap included telephones,
computer hardware, monitors, automobile parts, and diesel
generators.
</P>
<P>
Some customs clerks were found to have been involved in the
illegal transactions. 
