<HEADLINE> 5 Mourners Killed in N. Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Five mourners are feared dead and
over 60 others injured in a traffic accident in northern Zambia
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when the driver of the truck they were
travelling in allegedly failed to negotiate a corner within the
cemetery at Kawama in Ndola after a burial, the Zambia Daily Mail
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
One woman was instantly killed while several others sustained
serious injuries and were rushed to the Ndola Central Hospital,
where some of them died later.
</P>
<P>
A policeman at the hospital said the driver of the truck who
sustained minor injuries will be subjected to laboratory test to
determine if he was drunk or not.
</P>
<P>
Times of Zambia quoted the driver as saying that he lost
control of the truck as he was turning into the road leading out
of the cemetery after mourners had finished burying their dead
relative. 
</P>
