<HEADLINE> Shanghai's IT Industry Reports High Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's information
technology (IT) industry generated 38.7 billion yuan in output
value for the first half of this year, an increase of 23 percent
over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
More than one-tenth of the city's total IT products during the
time were exported to the United States, Japan and some other
countries.
</P>
<P>
The pretax profits of the industry grew 13 percent on a year-on-
year basis to hit 2.7 billion yuan in January-June.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, which has set the goal of becoming an international
information center in the near future, has listed the IT industry
as one of the key development areas of the local economy.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, the city has fostered a series of
profitable IT products like large-scale integrated circuits,
computers, and mobile telecommunications equipment.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show Shanghai manufactures one-fifth of China
's integrated circuits, one-third of its telecommunications
equipment, and 30 percent of IC cards.  
</P>
</TEXT>
