<DOCNO> XIE19990803.0223 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yangtze River Floodwaters Receding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 3 (Xinhua) --Floodwaters on the main course of
the Yangtze River have been receding now that rainfall on the
river valley has decreased.
</P>
<P>
The Yangtze River Water Conservation Committee in Wuhan, the
capital of Hubei Province, reports that water levels at most
hydrology stations have been falling over the past few days. The
level at Shashi went back to 41.8 meters by 8:00 A.M. Monday from
the danger line of 43 meters.
</P>
<P>
As a result of decreased water from the upper reaches and
Dongting Lake, the Wuhanguan station at Wuhan recorded a level of
27.73 meters at 08:00 A.M. Monday, which was half a meter above
the danger line.
</P>
<P>
Water levels are expected to continue to drop for the next
several days and the level at Wuhanguan will go below the danger
line tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Flooding on the Yangtze since late June has swollen the Yangtze,
bringing pressure on anti-flood efforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
