<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Women Soccer Craze Unabated in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The third Chinese women soccer
superleague found itself basking in the aftereffect of the third
World Cup in the United States concluded about half a month ago as
its opening round this season was greeted by a record capacity
crowd.
</P>
<P>
The eight-team superleague, which kicked off on Sunday
afternoon when the men's league also was in action, showed little
sign that it is still struggling in the shadow of the men soccer.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the rate of admission in the four venues, Zhejiang
Sports Center, where Liberation Army team host the Sichuan squad,
ranked forefront with a record attendance of 12,000 although both
teams have few internationals to show off.
</P>
<P>
Henan Provincial Stadium in Zhengzhou also found with
surprising delight that over ten thousand fans swarmed inside, a
spectucular scene which has been a luxury to the Chinese women
soccer.
</P>
<P>
The newly-built 4,000-seat Shandong Qilu Petrochemical Stadium,
where the superleague opening ceremony was held, was filled with a
sell-out enthusiasts. Those who failed to get tickets tried to
watch from the top of the highrise buildings or climbed up tall
trees just to feast their eyes.
</P>
<P>
According to the organisers, the 4,000 tickets, valued at RMB
20 yuan (about 2.5 U.S. dollars) were all sold out three days in
advance.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Shijingshan Stadium, which is home to Beijing Chengjian
Team with six internationals, welcomed not only its first downpour
after days of scorching heat but also 9,000 fans who hung a banner
reading "we will forvere support you Beijing women soccer".
</P>
<P>
The unexpected popularity of women soccer league sent a great
encouragement to the soccer officials, who have been baffled by
the sticky issue of developing women soccer market.
</P>
<P>
"The enthusiasm in the opening round indicates that women
soccer market has a promising future." said Lang Xiaonong,
director of the competition department of the Chinese Football
Association.
</P>
<P>
"The women superleague is popular partly for the fans who are
willing to cheer the women soccer who have garnered honors on
international scences, and partly for its charm has increased."
Lang said.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts also attributed the emergence of such amazingly
big crowd to the performances of women players, in particular the
national team who won the silver medal at the third Women's World
Cup.
</P>
<P>
The coaches and players, who have for long played to entertain
themselves, also popped their eyes and felt at a loss how to
behave properly in front of such a big crowd.
</P>
<P>
Wang Haiming, the head coach of Beijing Chengjian team, which
was sponsored by Beijing City-building Group, could not but reveal
his excitement, saying his side had a feeling of being pampered by
fans.
</P>
<P>
"It is really moving, I have not expected that. We will go all
out this season to return our gratitude for their unselfish
support." said Wang.
</P>
<P>
In Zhengzhou where the Shanghai team took on the hosting Henan
outfit, Sun Wen and Fan Yunjie, the internationals from each side,
became the focus of attention as the fans stood in the way of the
possible routes to team buses to get their autographs.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the men's league fans, there was an evident
increase of female fans. Two girs who had prepared horns for the
match said: "We are very proud of the Chinese women soccer. As one
member of the women family, we of course should cheer them and
show our firm support to them." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
