<HEADLINE> Asia's Tallest Man Dies in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The tallest man in Asia has died in
Bangladesh's southeastern district of Comilla, The Independent
daily newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Mohammad Yunus Mia, 7.6 feet (231.6 centimeters) in height and
believed to be the tallest man in Asia, died at the age of 52 on
Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Mia was a peon of a local office and had been suffering from
diabetes, family members said.
</P>
<P>
He was laid to rest Tuesday morning at his village graveyard at
a ceremony attended by local government officials. 
</P>
