<HEADLINE> Exports in Philippines Up 13.6 Pct in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine exports rose in the
first six months of this year by 13.6 percent to 15.8 billion U.S.
dollars from 13.9 billion dollars last year, the National
Statistics Office said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Export earnings for June reached 2.85 billion dollars, up 19.5
percent from 2.39 billion dollars a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Electronic equipment and parts remained the nation's top export
item, up 27.1 percent to 1.56 billion dollars in June and
accounting for 54.9 percent of the total revenue.
</P>
<P>
However, articles of wearing apparel and clothing accessories,
as the second top earner with sales amounting to 212.84 million
dollars, went down by 7.9 percent from 231.17 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The United States remained the country's top export market,
buying 937.28 million dollars worth of goods, or 32.8 percent of
the total receipts.
</P>
<P>
The next two major foreign markets were Japan with 13.4 percent
of the total receipts, and Singapore with an 8.1 percent share.
</P>
</TEXT>
