<HEADLINE> Indonesian Minister Calls For Punishment for Kurniawan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Minister of Sports
and Youth Affairs Agung Laksono called for harsh punishment for
the country's best striker Kurniawan Dwi Julianto, who was tested
positive for doping, The Indonesian Observer reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The harsh punishment, according to the minister, is intended to
give a warning to other athletes.
</P>
<P>
"Being eliminated from the Southeast Asian (SEA) Games
contingent is not enough. A more severe punishment should be
sought. He should be laid off for a long time if needed," Agung
said.
</P>
<P>
SEA Games training director Imron Z.S. said that Kurniawan, 23,
tested positive for amphetamines after the National Sports Council
(KONI) and the Jakarta doping laboratory conducted the tests in
June and July.
</P>
<P>
"A punitive act should not be looked at as killing off an
athlete's career. How could we stand having a player with such
mentality? And I hope others can learn from this case," he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Kurniawan admitted to being stunned by the finding,
which may spoil his career as a player. 
