<HEADLINE> 8 Soldiers Killed and Policemen Kidnapped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, August 2 (Xinhua)-- Eight soldiers of the
Colombian army were killed in the conflict starting on Sunday with
the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) in Urba area,
northwest of the country.
</P>
<P>
Sources of the military forces said Monday that another eight
policemen were kidnapped by insurgents in Narino, Anitioquia
locality, whose barracks were destroyed partly.
</P>
<P>
The conflict began in the rural zone of Apartado municipality,
Antioquia department, about 400 km northeast of Bogota.
</P>
<P>
Police and armed troops Sunday arrived at the sugar and coffee-
producing town of some 4,000 residents, where 300 rebels aimed
their attack at the police station defended by about 35 officers.
</P>
<P>
FARC, the biggest and oldest guerrilla group in Colombia, is
holding negotiations with the government since January, but they
oppose to create an international commission of verification.
</P>
<P>
There is no cease-fire in effect in the country where a 35-year-
long civil war has caused thousands of lives and huge material
losses. 
</P>
