<HEADLINE> Hungary Promotes Breast-feeding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The Hungarian Health Ministry
has decided to forbid advertisement of any foodstuff for babies
under six months of age in an effort to promote breast-feeding.
</P>
<P>
The ministry made the announcement at a press conference on
Breast-feeding Week, which falls in the first week of August, as
designated by the World Health Organization in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The government has ordered enterprises producing nutritious
food for babies under six months not to advertise their products,
the Health Ministry State Secretary Erzsebet Pusztai said.
</P>
<P>
Breast milk is rich in nutrition and is irreplaceable by any
manufactured foodstuff, he added.
</P>
<P>
The decision, which has been agreed upon by all related
enterprises and dealers, will take effect soon, Pusztai said.
</P>
</TEXT>
