<HEADLINE> 14 Kilos of Gold Seized at Sri Lanka's Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan Customs officers have
seized 120 gold slabs weighing 14 kilograms at the Bandaranaike
International Airport in the north suburb of Colombo, police
sources said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The gold slabs worth 7.8 million rupees (110,000 U.S. dollars)
were concealed in a special jacket worn under the shirt by an
Indian male passenger, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The man, who was a frequent traveler to Sri Lanka, claimed to
be a transit passenger on his way to Male, the Maldives, but was
unable to produce the air ticket for the connecting flight.
</P>
<P>
The Customs officers suspect the passenger, who arrived from
Dubai on Sunday, brought the gold to smuggle it in through local
agents.
</P>
<P>
The passenger was released but the gold was detained for
further investigation by the Customs.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, one of the Indian's companions was
also nabbed with 70 gold slabs on an earlier occasion.
</P>
<P>
But the Customs released him with the gold since he produced
documents to corroborate that he was a transit passenger. 
</P>
</TEXT>
