<HEADLINE> Rebel Suicide Bomber's Picture Found by S.Lankan Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police investigating
the assassination of parliamentarian Neelan Thiruchelvam have
found a photograph of the Tamil rebel suicide bomber at a Colombo
lodge where he had been hiding, police said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Thiruchelvam, a Tamil parliamentarian and vice-president of the
Tamil United Liberation Front, was killed in a suicide bombing
attack by the rebel at a stone's throw from his home in Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The bomber jumped off the back of a motor cyclist and onto
Thiruchelvam's car as it approached a busy intersection.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said a special police team has also found
several travel documents including the suicide bomber's passport.
</P>
<P>
They said police had obtained several vital leads after
questioning people who were alleged to have associated with the
suicide bomber.
</P>
<P>
The suicide bomber had come to the city early last year on the
pretext of seeking employment abroad, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The suicide bomber had not given his correct name and address
to the lodge's owner, the sources said, adding that police are
awaiting a comprehensive report of the government analyst in
connection with the killing.
</P>
<P>
The suicide bomber was sent by rebels of the Liberation Tigers
of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) who have been fighting for a separate Tamil
state in the north and east of the country since 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
