<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The board of directors of the
Egyptian Football Federation (EFF) and the team's coach became the
victims of Egypt's 5-1 humiliation by Saudi Arabia in the
Confederation Cup last week as they handed in the resignation
Monday amid widespread shock and blistering criticism at home.
</P>
<P>
Following a meeting of EFF's board of directors, its president,
Samir Zaher, headed to Prime Minister Kamal el-Ganzoury's office
to submit the resignation of the nine-member body. The team's
coach, Mahmoud el-Gohary, also resigned.
</P>
<P>
