el-Ganzoury detailing why the team, which returned in triumph in
February 1998 after winning the African Cup soccer tournament,
suffered such a humiliating loss.
</P>
<P>
The players had complained that the criticism was too hard on
them, saying that Paraguayan referee Ubaldo Aquino expelled three
Egyptian players during the game, leaving only eight to compete
against Saudi Arabia's 11 players.
</P>
<P>
Egypt did not qualify for the second round of the tournament
after it tied 2-2 with Bolivia and Mexico and was humiliated 5-1
by Saudi Arabia. 
