<HEADLINE> Temple to Be Built at Lumbini Gardens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A temple is to be built at the
Lumbini Gardens, with the stone slab which the Siddartha Gautam
stepped on at the time of his birth placed in a visible position,
the official RSS reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The stone was unearthed in the course of excavations carried
out at the site of the original temple of Mayadevi, mother of the
Historical Buddha.
</P>
<P>
It was on the basis of this stone that the discovery of the
inner sanctum of the original temple was announced.
</P>
<P>
The latest excavations at the temple site were carried out
between 1992 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
An agreement was reached earlier between the Japan Buddhist
Federation and the Lumbini Development Trust on renovation of the
Mayadevi Temple with 1.3 million U.S. dollars in assistance from
the federation. 
</P>
