<HEADLINE> 2 Killed in Explosion in Palembang, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A strong explosion Monday rocked
Palembang, provincial capital of Indonesia's South Sumatera,
killing two people and injuring three others while damaging five
houses, Antara News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bodies were found buried in the rubble of their houses
after the explosion which occurred in a scrap iron dump.
</P>
<P>
The explosion happened only two meters from Eddyson's house
which was also used to store scrap iron, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion resulted in a traffic snarl lasting several hours
as police had blocked the road leading to the site.
</P>
<P>
Police could not confirm the exact cause of the explosion as it
was still under investigation. But rumors have it that it might
have been a bomb which had been brought to the dump as a piece of
scrap iron. 
</P>
</TEXT>
