<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Close Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange
closed down on Monday with the Benchmark IPC index falling 153.58
points, or 2.92 percent, at 5,106.77.
</P>
<P>
Operators changed 57.032 million shares for about 83.311
million U.S. dollars against 78.798 million shares at a value of
95.025 million dollars on Friday, when the bourse closed their
weekly session.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.50 to one dollar for
sale and 9.20 for purchase in the main exchange houses of the
Mexico city, the same as those on Friday. 
</P>
