<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greene Impressed MAI Galan Athletics Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 2 (Xinhua) -- American sprint star Maurice
Greene hit an impressive double as he tied Ben Johnson's meet
record in the 100m race and broke Carl Lewis' stadium mark in the
200m at the MAI Galan meet at Malmo, Sweden on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Greene, who set a new world record of 9.79 seconds last month
in Athens, did not start as strong as compatriot Dennis Mitchell
who led halfway through, but he surged ahead and won on a time of
10.05 in the showcase race. Jon Drummond, Greene's training
partner, finished third in 10.17.
</P>
<P>
Johnson set the Malmo Stadium record in 1987, a few weeks
before the Canadian won the event in world-record time in the
World Championships in Rome.
</P>
<P>
Less than an hour after the 100m race, Greene clocked a time of
20.16 in the 200m, 0.11 seconds faster than Lewis' meet record set
in 1983.
</P>
<P>
Inger Miller, the Olympic and world champion in the 400 relay,
eased to a winning time of 11.19 seconds in the women's 100m
despite a head wind of 1.1 meters per second.
</P>
<P>
Marie Jose Perec of France, the 200 and 400 champion in the
1996 Olympics, timed 23.57 to finish second in the women's 200 in
her second race, close to Christine Bloomfield of Britain who won
the race in 23.45. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
