<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Enjoys Trade Surplus in 1st Half of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia ran a trade surplus of
10.12 billion U.S. dollars in the first half of 1999, Antara News
Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's exports in January-June were valued at 21.67
billion dollars, while the imports reached 11.55 billion dollars,
the Central Bureau of Statistics was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
But the exports dropped by 11.81 percent from the same period
of last year and the decline was the result of a 12.63 percent
drop in non-oil/gas exports from 20.51 billion dollars to 17.92
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, crude oil exports increased from 1.70
billion dollars to 1.84 billion dollars as a result of the oil
price hike on the world market from 15.94 dollars per barrel in
May 1999 to 15.95 dollars per barrel in June 1999.
</P>
<P>
Oil/gas imports dropped by 7.80 percent from 1.45 billion
dollars to 1.34 billion dollars, while non-oil/gas imports
declined by 13.87 percent from 11.85 billion dollars to 10.21
billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
