<HEADLINE> Courier Wins First Round in du Maurier Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 2 (Xinhua) -- American Jim Courier, the four-
time Grand Slam winner ranked 46th in the world, eliminated
Germany's Rainer Schuttler 7-6 (7-2), 6-2 on Monday in the first
round of the du Maurier Open tennis tournament in Montreal on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Seventh-seeded Marcelo Rios of Chile, a former No. 1 player,
withdrew from the event with a leg injury.
</P>
<P>
Two seeded players from Sweden lost Monday, No. 10 Thomas
Enqvist and No. 16 Jonas Bjorkman.
</P>
<P>
Enqvist, a finalist in the Australian Open, lost 6-4, 2-6, 7-5
to Arnaud Clement of France, while Bjorkman lost 6-2, 6-2 to Jiri
Novak of the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Among seeded players who entered the second round Monday were
No. 9 Nicolas Kiefer of Germany, a 6-2, 7-5 winner over Daniel
Vacek of the Czech Republic; 12th-seeded Vincent Spadea of the
United States, a 7-6 (7-3), 6-4 winner over Frederic Niemeyer of
Canada; and No. 15 Sebastien Grosjean of France, who edged Mark
Knowles of the Bahamas 6-2, 1-6, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
American Michael Chang, whose ranking has plunged to 64th,
defeated Slovakia's Jan Kroslak 5-7, 7-5, 6-1. 
</P>
