<HEADLINE> 359 Kilo of Cocaine Pulp Seized in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The highway police have seized 359
kilograms of basic cocaine pulp in the southeast of Peru, the
highway police said Monday.
</P>
<P>
While inspecting a refrigerator truck on the Huanta-Huncayo
road in Ayacucho department last weekend, a road patrol detected
basic cocaine pulp in 284 parcels, covered with a substance to
throw off the scent of drug-detector dogs, said the police.
</P>
<P>
Basic cocaine pulp can be transformed into pure cocaine, which
is then trafficked to the United States and Europe, the highway
police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
