<HEADLINE> 8 Die When Colombian Bus Tumbles into River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 2 (Xinhua)-- At least eight persons
died and 35 were injured Monday when a bus fell into a river in
Antioquia department, northeast of Colombia.
</P>
<P>
The coach, carrying members of a football team, was traveling
at a high rate of speed when it fell into the Dormilon River. The
driver reportedly lost control of the vehicle, police said.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened near the towns of San Luis and Cocurna,
about 330 kilometers north of Santafe de Bogota, the capital of
Colombia.
</P>
<P>
The football team was returning from a match played in San Luis.
