<DOCNO> XIE19990803.0299 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Croatian Suker Joins Arsenal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Croatian football star Davor Suker
admitted Monday he has taken a massive pay cut to join Arsenal as
the 3.5 million pounds replacement for money-mad Nicolas Anelka as
Highbury's top Gunner.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old player was on the equivalent of 40,000 pounds a
week with Real Madrid where walk-out rebel Anelka, 20, is due to
pitch up this week on even higher wages - and with a mouth-
watering seven-year contract.
</P>
<P>
But both Arsenal, who will receive close to 24 million pounds
in five instalments from Real for the moody French international,
and Suker are convinced they have the best of the deal.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal manager Arsene Wenger has labelled him a goalscorer in
the Ian Wright mould to supplement the power and artistry of
Dennis Bergkamp and Nwankwo Kanu in the twin-quest to wrest
Premiership -and European - supremacy from Manchester United.
</P>
<P>
"It would not be right for me to give you the figures," said
Wenger, "but I can tell you Suker has taken a substantial cut in
wages.
</P>
<P>
"This is very unusual. He can, of course, improve what he earns
under our bonus scheme by helping us to win trophies - just as the
rest of the squad can - but every new signing is a gamble and I
admire him for the one he is taking by coming here.
</P>
<P>
"He had other opportunities in Greece and Turkey as well as in
Spain which were very financially attractive but he has chosen to
come to Arsenal and he's happy to fit into the wages structure
here.
</P>
<P>
"I have always been determined not to harm that pay policy but
I needed an experienced striker and now I have one at the right
price who also has great ability, spirit and desire. He has the
talent to be a great success here and he has the right spirit for
us." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
