<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Finishes First Phase Of World Largest Ship Lock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, August 3 (Xinhua) -- China has completed digging work
on the world's largest ship lock project at the Three Gorges on
the northern bank of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
Engineers say that this provides a solid foundation for the
first group of generators.
</P>
<P>
The ship lock is over 6,400 meters long and is 113 meters tall.
It is being carved out of granite and will take workers 5 years to
remove 40 million cubic meters of granite.
</P>
<P>
The concrete pouring has started and the lock is expected to be
operational in July, 2003. 
</P>
</TEXT>
