<BODY>
<HEADLINE> USA Sweeps Mountain Bike Titles in Pam Am Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The United States made
it a sweeping victory in the Pan Am mountain bike competitions as
both men's and women's golds fell to their hands here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Alison Dunlap, ranked third in the world going into the Pan Am
Games, clocked two hours nine minutes and 44.68 seconds to triumph
in the women's event.
</P>
<P>
Her male teammate Edward Larsen, the only US cyclist to ever
compete in all four cycling championships (road, track, mountain
and cyclo-cross), registered a time of 2:19:21.87 to capture the
men's gold.
</P>
<P>
Both of them will compete in the Pan Am Games road race on
August 4.
</P>
<P>
The mountain bike event is a mass start competition that is
held on a circuit course comprised of forest roads, off-road
trails and unpaved dirt or gravel roads. The number of laps
defends on the level of competitors and the length of the course.
</P>
<P>
The mountain bike made its Olympics debut in 1996 in Atlanta
and was first contested at the Pan Am Games in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
