<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Aboriginal Art on Display at U.N. Headquarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A major exhibition of
Australian aboriginal art, "Indigenous Art of the Dreamtime,"
kicked off Monday at the United Nations headquarters in New York.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, first of its kind at the world body, is
co-sponsored by the U.N. Department of Public Information and the
Australian Mission to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
A companion exhibition, featuring a further 30 works of
indigenous art, will be on display at the Australian Mission to
the United Nations and Australian Consulate-General premises on
August 4-25.
</P>
<P>
The exhibitions bring together some of the leading exponents
of Central Australian Desert art, including acknowledged masters
of the genre, such as Emily Kame Kngwarreye and Clifford Possum
Tjapalatjarri.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
